1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §2054, sub-§1, ¶K is enacted to read:
3 K. "Variable-message sign" means a traffic control device on which a message can be
4 displayed and changed manually, electrically, mechanically or electromechanically to
5 provide information about traffic congestion, traffic accidents, maintenance operations,
6 adverse weather conditions, roadway conditions, organized events or other necessary
7 information.
8 Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §2054, sub-§12 is enacted to read:
9 12. Variable-message signs. The operator of an authorized public service vehicle
10 may use a variable-message sign on the authorized public service vehicle while the vehicle
11 is stationary and engaged in roadside repair, loading or unloading a vehicle, vehicle
12 recovery or general traffic control. The Commissioner of Public Safety may adopt rules as
13 necessary for the purpose of implementing this subsection. Rules adopted pursuant to this
14 subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill allows the operator of an authorized public service vehicle to use a variable-
1177 message sign on the authorized public service vehicle while the vehicle is stationary and
1188 engaged in roadside repair, loading or unloading a vehicle, vehicle recovery or general
1199 traffic control.
